But, no one yelled at me. No one called me stupid. No one told me to stop being a baby. No one told me I'm wasting my time. No one told me I was making a mess. No one told me I'm just wasting space. 
And I had the space for it, it didn't get too overwhelming to make, I didn't have to throw away 3 bags of trash to make space for it, I didn't have to beg my partner to help, I didn't stress about what I was doing, I didn't worry about not having the materials I wanted to do it right

This might all seem so silly but to me it's huge.
I grew up in a family telling me everything I was doing was wrong, then had a depressed fiance while also depressed myself, so out apartment was constantly filthy and you couldn't see the floor 

I've completely turned my life around in the past 7 months, I'm single and free and just... Man I'm just happy. 

All the stuffed animals have names, some are obvious and some aren't, but they all wanted to come join me in my blanket fort 

The rest of the living room is a mess but no where near as bad as it used to be, and the space in general just feels bigger 
I've wanted to make a blanket fort like this my entire life, I think it's going to stick around for a while 

TL:DR, I have a blanket fort and you don't.

Edit: all vents are clear! Everything has been carefully constructed to make sure there's no hazards! 
I have no appropriate snacks cause I'm mega broke but this will be sticking around for a while!

Second edit: I'm also gonna sneakily place my PayPal riiiiight here for snack funds @ThaliaWho</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/yaplrH5</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ThaliaWho]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Shameless repost from a comment...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/4yHx2Mb</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/cHJlfEm.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/4yHx2Mb</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[TomatoPepper]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Fierce Smol One</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/p3ZMsqv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/yj2DMSF.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#puppy #smol #adorable #smallbutfierce #aww</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/p3ZMsqv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MartyIndependence]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The American Experience</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9XuYMME</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ILottp4.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9XuYMME</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[candiedyms]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Can Imgur help me in remembering my brother?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/cdjY05Z</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IqlLLEU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I lost my brother last weekend...
He was severely disabled with epilepsy, but he was always happy and laughing. His condition was chronic so over the years he lost the ability to walk and talk. And yet he was always full of joy; grinning and laughing when you would talk to him. He would smack things with his hand as a way of interacting with his surroundings so we would have lots of fun doing high-fives.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HANG5Ba.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Its hard looking back on all the memories, but I know its really important to process through the grief. I know Imgur is a big mix of lots of beliefs and backgrounds; my family is Christian and it helps to picture him in Heaven in a healed and healthy body. When he was in hospice, I kept imagining him being able to run through green fields and play and laugh. The Bible talks about the Earth being redeemed and being made perfect again (we can all agree things are pretty messed up now, right) so its nice to think about him enjoying Heaven by doing all the things he wasn't able to in this life.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tNk8qcL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>There are so many talented artists on here so I was hoping I could get some help with making a memorial picture/painting of him. I have this image of him laughing and running through green, grassy fields. Would any artistic imgurians be willing to help me make a painting that I can remember him by? 

I have included some pictures from his life that I hope will help. If more would be useful, I am currently going through our old photos and making digital copies. Hopefully, I will have more soon. 

Thanks in advance</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1I80Vv4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xebcX0H.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KBpgsp7.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6p3uxDp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NXq1cMF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nqQlkIl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/krVr0zB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IVaKAIV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SrMgRKQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>See you on the other side Mathew!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/cdjY05Z</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[chillychiweenie]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Animal Bonding</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/KIHyezv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ei9mRWR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KIHyezv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[cenkiss2331]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I hate to kill you.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/eW5nTB5</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/661Tm2H.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Source: The Princess Bride (1987) #intergalacticqualitygifs (Check WiFi before entering.)

